keen_reloaded — Licensing
==========================

This project is a non-commercial fan work. It contains three different kinds of
material, each with a different legal status. Please read this file in full.


1. SOURCE CODE — MIT License
----------------------------

All original source code in this repository (everything under `src/`, `tools/`,
`tests/`, the `Makefile`, the `addons/` vendored code, and project scripts) is
licensed under the terms of the MIT License (see the full text below).

In short: you may use, copy, modify, merge, publish, distribute, sublicense,
and/or sell copies of the code, for any purpose — including commercial —
provided you include the copyright notice and this permission notice.

The MIT License applies only to the SOURCE CODE, not to the derived artwork or
the Commander Keen intellectual property (see section 2).


2. COMMANDER KEEN IP & DERIVED ART — NOT LICENSED
-------------------------------------------------

*Commander Keen* and all related characters, names, story, and concepts are the
property of **id Software**. This project is not affiliated with, endorsed by,
or associated with id Software.

The sprite and tile art in `assets/sprites/` and `assets/tilesets/` is DERIVED
from the original *Commander Keen* games (edited: upscaled from 16px to 64px,
and otherwise retouched for use in a modern engine). This art is a derivative
work of copyrighted material that this project does not own and therefore
CANNOT license. It is included for non-commercial fan use only and remains the
property of id Software.

The "Invasion of the Vorticons" title art is likewise id Software's property.

Nothing in this repository grants any rights to the *Commander Keen*
intellectual property or the derived artwork. If you wish to reuse the source
code (section 1) you should supply your own original assets.


3. AUDIO & HUD ICONS — CC0 (Public Domain)
------------------------------------------

All audio in `assets/audio/` and the HUD icons (`tools/gen_hud_icons.gd`) are
programmatically generated original works dedicated to the public domain under
CC0 1.0. No attribution required. See `assets/audio/LICENSE.txt`.


4. THIRD-PARTY TOOLS — THEIR OWN LICENSES
-----------------------------------------

- **Godot Engine** — MIT License (https://godotengine.org/license)
- **GUT (Godot Unit Test)** — MIT License, vendored in `addons/gut/`
  (https://github.com/bitwes/Gut)

These retain their respective licenses.


